# Code ownership and review routing.
#
# Order matters: more specific rules below override the global rule
# above them. The wildcard at the bottom guarantees every PR still gets
# human eyes if no specific rule matches.
#
# `@${OWNER}/compliance-review` is the placeholder team for compliance-
# sensitive paths. The team must be created in your GitHub org and
# populated with the designated compliance reviewers before branch
# protection on `main` can enforce it. Until the team exists, GitHub
# silently drops the entry and only @${OWNER} is requested.

# Compliance-sensitive paths — require both the global owner and the
# compliance-review team. These mirror the watched paths in
# `.github/workflows/trust-boundary.yml`. The bootstrap script
# substitutes ${WATCHED_PATHS_AS_CODEOWNER_LINES} with one CODEOWNERS
# line per watched path glob.
#
# Example shape (the bootstrap script writes lines like these):
#   /internal/policy/             @${OWNER} @${OWNER}/compliance-review
#   /internal/audit/              @${OWNER} @${OWNER}/compliance-review
#
${WATCHED_PATHS_AS_CODEOWNER_LINES}

# Global fallback. Ensures every PR gets human eyes before merge.
*       @${OWNER}
